Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba briefed deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa on his scheduled visit to the USA for the forthcoming IMF and World Bank spring meetings. JOHANNESBURG Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has pledged his support for Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba as he showcases the country during his visit to the United States of America (USA) this week.Gigaba briefed Ramaphosa on Tuesday on his scheduled visit to the USA for the forthcoming International Monetary Fund and World Bank spring meetings, as well as further interactions with rating agencies.Ramaphosa explains what Gigiba s trip involves: This is continuous internal government briefing about what the minister is going to be doing. We are very supportive of the minister and his team as they are going to showcase South Africa to the world. At the same time, Business Leadership South Africa has requested a meeting with President Jacob Zuma to establish new terms of engagement to rebuild trust between business and government.It's calling on elected representatives in Parliament, the ruling party and its alliance partners to take immediate steps to reverse corruption and state capture in order to restore confidence in both the country's leadership and economy.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)